- content_for :title, "Assignment Experience Survey"

- content_for :header do
  .d-flex.align-items-center.flex-wrap.gap-2
    %h1.mb-0
      %i.bi.bi-clipboard2-check.me-2
      Assignment Experience Survey
    %span.badge.text-bg-warning
      %i.bi.bi-flask.me-1
      Beta
    %button.btn.btn-sm.btn-outline-info.rounded-circle{type: "button",
      title: "Learn how this identifiable assignment survey works; click for details",
      "aria-label": "About the Assignment Experience Survey",
      "aria-controls": "assignment-survey-page-info",
      "aria-expanded": "false",
      "data-bs-toggle": "collapse",
      "data-bs-target": "#assignment-survey-page-info"}
      %i.bi.bi-info-lg

.collapse.mb-3#assignment-survey-page-info
  .alert.alert-light.border
    %h3.fw-semibold.mb-2 Goal of this page
    %p
      Speak plainly about whether your assignments are understandable, possible, and relevant so expectations can improve.

    %h3.fw-semibold.mb-2 Context
    = render "shared/maap/definition"

    %h3.fw-semibold.mb-2 Specifics of this page
    %ul.mb-0
      %li Your name is attached to every draft and finalized response.
      %li Your employment managers and managerial hierarchy can read draft answers as they are saved.
      %li A finalized survey cannot be edited. You can start another survey later, and only your latest finalized version counts in current summaries.
      %li Ratings use six agreement choices with no neutral midpoint. Written comments are optional.
